### PART II: THE 3 SACRED TEMPLATES (12 pages)
*"Copy-paste these. Use them tomorrow. Modify later."*

#### Template 1: The Pulse (BLUES Mode)

**2.1 What It Is**
One-line status update. NOT a discussion. NOT a request.

**2.2 The Format (Strict)**
```
ðŸ‘¤ @username: [ðŸŸ¢ðŸŸ¡ðŸ”´] [What you're working on] [Progress %] [ETA or blocker]
```

**2.3 Examples (Good vs Bad)**

**âœ… GOOD:**
```
ðŸ‘¤ @alice: ðŸŸ¢ Payment gateway integration 75% done. On track for Friday.
ðŸ‘¤ @bob: ðŸŸ¡ Database research taking longer than expected. Need 2 more days.
ðŸ‘¤ @charlie: ðŸ”´ BEACON - Blocked on API access. Need Micro-GUSH with DevOps.
```

**âŒ BAD:**
```
ðŸ‘¤ @alice: Working on stuff. Making progress I think?
ðŸ‘¤ @bob: Database is complicated. Many options. Not sure which to pick. Thoughts?
ðŸ‘¤ @charlie: Hey @dave can you help me with that thing we discussed?
```

**Why the bad examples fail:**
- Alice: No specificity (what stuff? how much progress?)
- Bob: Turns pulse into discussion (belongs in GUSH)
- Charlie: Creates interruption (DM should be async question)

**2.4 Pulse Rhythm**

**Daily (High Impedance):** 
- Post time: Same time every day (e.g., 4pm)
- Thread: #pulse-updates
- No responses allowed in thread (strict rule)

**Weekly (Low Impedance):**
- Post time: Friday 3pm
- Same format, longer horizon

**2.5 AI Role in Pulse (Optional)**

If you have AI assistant:
```
Prompt: "Aggregate today's pulses into 3-sentence summary. 
Highlight: (1) Overall progress, (2) Blockers/BEACONs, (3) Merge opportunities."
```

**Manual alternative:** Facilitator does this Friday afternoon.

**2.6 The BEACON Protocol**

ðŸ”´ = "I'm blocked, need sync help NOW"

**What happens:**
1. BEACON posted in pulse
2. Facilitator (or AI) sees it within 2h
3. Micro-GUSH scheduled within 24h
4. Micro-GUSH: 15-30 min, just the blocker

**Example resolution:**
```
Monday 4pm: Charlie posts BEACON (API access)
Monday 5pm: Facilitator DMs Charlie + DevOps lead
Tuesday 10am: 20-min Micro-GUSH
Tuesday 10:20am: Charlie unblocked, continues work
```

**Estimate:** 4 pages

---

#### Template 2: Fork Declaration (BHO)

**2.7 What It Is**
"I'm disappearing for N days to work deeply. No interruptions. I'll merge back with results."

**2.8 The Format**
```markdown
# BHO Fork: [Topic Name]

**Forker:** @username
**Start Date:** YYYY-MM-DD
**Merge Promise:** YYYY-MM-DD (max 7 days recommended)
**Rationale:** [1-2 sentences why this needs isolation]

## Scope
I will explore:
- [Bullet 1]
- [Bullet 2]
- [Bullet 3]

## Out of Scope
I will NOT explore:
- [Boundary 1]
- [Boundary 2]

## Pulse Schedule
[Daily/Every 2 days] at [TIME] in #pulse-updates

## Merge Criteria
This fork is ready to merge when:
[Objective condition, e.g., "Prototype working + benchmark complete"]

## Merge Method
[Micro-GUSH on DATE] OR [Document + async review]
```

**2.9 Real Example**
```markdown
# BHO Fork: PostgreSQL vs MongoDB Evaluation

**Forker:** @marcus
**Start Date:** 2026-02-12
**Merge Promise:** 2026-02-16 (Friday)
**Rationale:** This decision needs deep research, not more opinions. 
I need 4 days of focused benchmarking.

## Scope
I will explore:
- Query performance (read/write benchmarks)
- Schema flexibility for our use case
- Team expertise required
- Migration complexity from current MySQL

## Out of Scope
I will NOT explore:
- NewSQL options (out of scope for this sprint)
- Cloud-hosted solutions (separate decision)

## Pulse Schedule
Daily at 4pm in #pulse-updates

## Merge Criteria
This fork is ready to merge when:
- Benchmark results documented
- 2-page comparison matrix complete
- Cost analysis done

## Merge Method
Micro-GUSH Friday 2pm (30 min) with architecture team
```

**2.10 When NOT to Fork**

âŒ Don't fork if:
- Decision is urgent (next 48h) â†’ Use GUSH instead
- You need input from others â†’ That's collaboration, not fork
- It's routine work â†’ Just do it in Study Hall

âœ… Fork if:
- High complexity requiring deep focus
- Exploring genuinely uncertain territory
- Team debate is circular (need divergence first)

**2.11 The Merge-Back Protocol**

**Option A: Micro-GUSH (Synchronous)**
- 15-30 min session
- Forker presents findings (5 min)
- Q&A (10 min)
- Decision or next steps (10 min)

**Option B: Document + Async Review**
- Forker writes 1-2 page summary
- Posts in #decisions channel
- 48h for async feedback
- If no major objections â†’ Adopted
- If objections â†’ Schedule GUSH

**Estimate:** 4 pages

---

#### Template 3: GUSH Agenda (Forced Convergence)

**2.12 What It Is**
Time-boxed (45-60 min MAX) session where team MUST produce a decision or deliverable.

**2.13 Pre-GUSH Checklist (24h before)**

**Mandatory pre-work:**
- [ ] Objective defined (single decision to make)
- [ ] Context document shared (2 pages max)
- [ ] All participants confirmed they've read it
- [ ] Facilitator assigned (can be human or AI)
- [ ] Timer set and visible

**If ANY checkbox is unchecked â†’ Postpone GUSH**

**2.14 The 45-Minute Template**
```markdown
# GUSH Session: [Decision Title]

**Date:** YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM
**Duration:** 45 minutes (HARD STOP)
**Participants:** @name1, @name2, @name3
**Facilitator:** @facilitator (or AI)
**Objective:** [Single decision to make]

## Agenda

### 0-5 min: Alignment Check
- Confirm everyone read pre-work
- Restate objective
- Set timer (visible to all)

### 5-15 min: Position A Presentation
- Presenter: @name1
- Format: 5-min pitch (slides optional)
- NO interruptions (questions held for debate)

### 15-25 min: Position B Presentation
- Presenter: @name2
- Format: Same as above

### 25-40 min: Structured Debate
- Round 1 (5 min): Questions for clarity
- Round 2 (5 min): Counter-arguments
- Round 3 (5 min): Synthesis attempts

### 40-45 min: Decision + Documentation
- Method: [Vote / Weighted criteria / Consensus / Facilitator call]
- Document: [Who/What/When/Why]
- Dissenters: "Disagree & Commit" acknowledgment

## Decision Record (Fill during session)

**Chosen Option:** [A / B / Hybrid / Postpone to DATE]

**Rationale:** 
[2-3 sentences explaining WHY]

**Dissenters:**
[Names who disagreed + their "Disagree & Commit" statement]

**Action Items:**
- [ ] @owner: [Task] by [DATE]
- [ ] @owner: [Task] by [DATE]

**Next Checkpoint:**
[When we review this decision]
```

**2.15 Example: SQL vs NoSQL Decision**
```markdown
# GUSH Session: Database Selection for User Service

**Date:** 2026-02-14 14:00
**Duration:** 45 minutes
**Participants:** @alice, @bob, @charlie, @dana, @eve
**Facilitator:** @charlie (neutral)
**Objective:** Choose PostgreSQL OR MongoDB for user service rewrite

## Pre-Work Shared
- Alice's 2-page case for PostgreSQL (shared Feb 13, 2pm)
- Bob's 2-page case for MongoDB (shared Feb 13, 2pm)
- All confirmed read âœ…

## Agenda Execution

### 0-5 min: Alignment
âœ… Everyone read both docs
âœ… Objective clear: Pick ONE, ship by March 1
âœ… Timer set, visible on Zoom

### 5-15 min: PostgreSQL Case (Alice)
Key points:
- ACID guarantees critical for user data
- Team already knows SQL
- Strong ecosystem
- Migration path clear

### 15-25 min: MongoDB Case (Bob)
Key points:
- Schema flexibility for evolving user model
- Better performance for read-heavy workload
- JSON-native (matches our API)
- Horizontal scaling easier

### 25-40 min: Debate
Q: What's our read/write ratio? â†’ 80/20 (Bob's point holds)
Q: How critical is ACID? â†’ Very (Alice's point holds)
Counter: PostgreSQL can scale horizontally too (Alice)
Counter: MongoDB has transactions now (Bob)

Synthesis attempt (Charlie): "Both are viable. Criteria?"

### 40-45 min: Decision

**Method:** Weighted criteria vote

| Criteria | Weight | PostgreSQL | MongoDB |
|----------|--------|------------|---------|
| ACID compliance | 40% | 10 | 7 |
| Performance | 30% | 7 | 9 |
| Team expertise | 20% | 9 | 5 |
| Migration cost | 10% | 8 | 6 |
| **Total** | | **8.5** | **7.3** |

**Chosen Option:** PostgreSQL

**Rationale:** 
ACID compliance is non-negotiable for user data. Performance difference is marginal for our scale. Team expertise reduces risk. We can optimize later if needed.

**Dissenters:**
- Bob: "I disagree with the weighting (performance should be 40%), but I commit to making PostgreSQL work and will lead the optimization effort."

**Action Items:**
- [ ] @alice: Create migration plan by Feb 17
- [ ] @dana: Set up PostgreSQL staging by Feb 18
- [ ] @bob: Lead performance optimization post-launch

**Next Checkpoint:** March 15 (review performance metrics)
```

**2.16 GUSH Anti-Patterns**

âŒ **The Endless GUSH:**
- Goes past 60 min
- "Just 5 more minutes..." â†’ NO. Stop. Schedule Part 2.

âŒ **The Unprepared GUSH:**
- No pre-work shared
- People read docs during session
- Result: Waste of time

âŒ **The Fake GUSH:**
- Decision already made privately
- GUSH is just theater
- Result: Team resentment

âŒ **The Multi-Objective GUSH:**
- Trying to decide 3 things in one session
- Result: Decides none well

**Estimate:** 4 pages

